# Next.js Patterns

## App Router Structure
- **Route Organization**: Use [web/src/app/](mdc:web/src/app/) for App Router
- **Page Components**: Place page components in appropriate route folders
- **Layout Components**: Use layout.tsx for shared layouts
- **Loading States**: Implement loading.tsx for loading states
- **Error Handling**: Use error.tsx for error boundaries
- **Not Found**: Use not-found.tsx for 404 pages

## Web Folder
- All Next.js code lives in [web/](mdc:web/)
- Templates are generated via `npm run generate-templates` (reads from ../template)
- Build: `npm run build` in web/ – runs generate-templates then next build

## Performance
- **Client Components**: Use "use client" only where needed (e.g. Wizard with JSZip)
- **Static Generation**: Prefer static where possible
- **Code Splitting**: Use dynamic imports for heavy deps
